1.title: Nashville
1.plot: Taylor Lewan shares some surf and turf; Steve and Landyn Hutchinson show Jackie how true foodies eat; Anthony Fasano surprises Jackie with French cuisine.

2.title: Charlotte
2.plot: Luke Kuechly shows his go-to meal just blocks from home; Thomas Davis and his wife, Kelly, enjoy soul food; Ryan Kalil petitions to get his favorite sandwich named after him at a local pub.

3.title: Miami
3.plot: Michael Thomas and wife Gloria share a hidden gem for sushi; Brandon Marshall surprises Jackie with octopus at a steak house; Jordan Cameron shows off gourmet grilled cheese from his favorite food truck.

4.title: Atlanta
4.plot: Jackie goes to Atlanta's Little Italy with Brooks Reed and his wife Natalie; a king-sized steak fit for a lineman; healthy Mexican food with Ricardo Allen and his wife Grace.

5.title: New York
5.plot: Nick Mangold reveals the ultimate lineman-sized burger; Will Tye teaches his touchdown moves at his favorite steak house; Mark Herzlich and Danielle introduce Jackie to waterfront Italian dining with a view.

6.title: New Orleans
6.plot: Jackie's in Who Dat Nation to dine with Saints star RB Mark Ingram at his go-to hideaway. James Laurinaitis and wife Shelly introduce the finer side of seafood off Bourbon Street, and Keenan Lewis teaches crawfish technique at his old stomping grounds.

imdb.plot outline: Hosted by TV personality Jackie Long (wife of NFL star Jake Long) and powered by famous professional athletes. Follow Jackie across America as she dines with athletes and their significant others. Each episode takes place in a different city with Jackie visiting three restaurants each with a different NFL player. The show will focus on local establishments and will highlight the players' favorite meals. Jackie will interact with the players, their significant others, customers and the chef/kitchen staff.
